description: Vicky Form is a lingerie, cosmetics, and clothing company.
Victory Farms uses cutting edge technology to farm tilapia in Lake Victoria at scale, delivering fresh fish throughout Western Kenya and Nairobi.
VIDA (Verified Identity for All) provides a trusted digital identity platform.
Vispera offers image recognition-based retail execution and tracking services to grocery retailers and suppliers so that they can transform the way they monitor their field operations.
VisualNACert’s all-in-one farm management software powered by geospatial mapping intelligence digitally visualizes land so that it can be better managed.
VivaReal is an online real estate portal that enables its users to sell, buy, rent, or invest in residential and commercial properties throughout Brazil. It was acquired by OLX Brazil in 2020.

Vive Agro offers clients washed, cut, and ready-to-use vegetables, helping restaurants reduce their costs by up to 22%. Meanwhile, the farmers who work with Vive Agro obtain better prices on their produce and receive best practices from Vive Agro’s agronomists.
Vivo Activewear is a Kenyan retail brand that designs and produces quality clothing for African women.
VN Global is a law focused company that specializes in debt collection.
Volt Lines is a subscription-based transportation network serving corporate customers in Turkey, combining the comfort of a car with the affordability of a public transit network.
VU Security is a consumer mobile cybersecurity company.
Wavetec provides customer experience solutions and financial information display solutions on an international scale.
We Are Knitters provides an outlet for mindfulness and creativity through its curated knitting kits and global knitting community.

Welle Laser produces advanced fiber-optic laser cutting machines and intelligent remote monitoring software, working mainly in large-scale industry segments to help clients optimize their production lines and increase their productivity.
WellSpring leverages highly trained counselors, an accredited, age-specific curriculum, and state-of-the-art facilities to provide unique experiential learning programs for children.
WHILL designs and creates personal mobility products for indoor and outdoor applications.
Whites is a Saudi Arabian brick-and-mortar retail store that sells pharmaceutical products and cosmetics.
Wholemeaning allows companies to automatically review customer feedback and receive business insights.
Widetech designs and develops management software for vehicle fleets, fixed assets, and field personnel in Latin America that incorporates GPS and GPRS tracking technologies.
WiGroup is a software business that enables retailers to integrate into one platform and access any mobile transaction application.
